<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="129" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,345,895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,345,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to previous species but differing as follows: parapsidal furrows shallow and finely punctate, anterior margin of scutellum with an irregular and narrow transverse furrow (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1095,380,407]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–8. 3–4, 7, Calligaster ilocana Selis, sp. nov. 5–6, 8, Calligaster williamsi Bequaert, 1940. 3, 5, Head of male in frontal view. 4, 6, Head of female in frontal view. 7–8, Mesoscutum and scutellum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), scutellum entirely matt with sparse fine punctures, apical emargination of male clypeus semicircular and as deep as wide (
<figureCitation box="[1206,1274,415,442]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–8. 3–4, 7, Calligaster ilocana Selis, sp. nov. 5–6, 8, Calligaster williamsi Bequaert, 1940. 3, 5, Head of male in frontal view. 4, 6, Head of female in frontal view. 7–8, Mesoscutum and scutellum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), face entirely black in both sexes, female clypeus more sparsely punctured on the disc (
<figureCitation box="[999,1069,450,477]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–8. 3–4, 7, Calligaster ilocana Selis, sp. nov. 5–6, 8, Calligaster williamsi Bequaert, 1940. 3, 5, Head of male in frontal view. 4, 6, Head of female in frontal view. 7–8, Mesoscutum and scutellum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); apical part of aedeagus nearly straight in lateral view, ventral lobes of aedeagus in lateral view subtriangular and pointed and as wide as base of apical part of aedeagus, anteroventral lobe of digitus pointed and forming an acute angle (
<figureCitation box="[1157,1241,519,545]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[225,1363,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[225,1363,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. Male genitalia, from left to right: aedeagus in lateral view, aedeagus in ventral view, digitus and volsella. 9, Calligaster ilocana Selis, sp. nov. 10, Calligaster williamsi Bequaert, 1940." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669330/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
